problem:
Two circles are centered at the origin, as shown.  The point $P(143,24)$ is on the larger circle and the point $S(0,k)$ is on the smaller circle.  If $QR=35$, what is the value of $k$? [asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(.7pt)+fontsize(10pt));
dotfactor=4;
draw(Circle((0,0),110)); draw(Circle((0,0),145));
dot((0,0)); dot((110,0)); dot((145,0)); dot((0,110)); dot((143,24));
draw((0,0)--(143,24));
label("$S (0,k)$",(0,7.5),W);
draw((148,0)--(0,0)--(0,148),Arrows(TeXHead));
draw((-148,0)--(0,0)--(0,-148));

label("$x$",(148,0),E); label("$y$",(0,148),N); label("$P(143,24)$",(143,24),NE);

label("$O$",(0,0),SW); label("$Q$",(110,0),SW); label("$R$",(145,0),SE);

[/asy]
